### political setting (continued) ###

3 aspects of pc that shape american federalism
    perception of what gov is and what is expected
    kind of people involved in politics
        elected officials
    
perceptions of american political order
    marketplace
        primary rels in society are about bargaining and self-interest
        power: who gets what, when, and how much
    commonwealth
        citizens have undivided interests and coop to create and maintain the best gov to implement certain moral principles
        justice: continual dev of the good society
    role of government to balance the two